The pipeline editor allows to design the Data Transformation project visually.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

When you create a new Data Transformation project, by default it contains three basic building blocks: Reader, Mapper, Writer. Starting from this configuration, you can edit and configure the default resources or create new ones, as described in the following sections.![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Creating a new resource
To create a new resource and connect it to the pipeline later, follow these steps:

- Click **Create Resource **at the top of the pipeline editor area.

- Select the type of resource to create; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Enter the required parameters; for example:![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **CONTINUE **to proceed.

The new resource is added to the pipeline area but is not connected to any elements:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to connect pipeline elements, see [Connecting pipeline elements](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-pipeline-editor#connecting-pipeline-elements) below.

For more information on how to configure pipeline elements, see: [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

## Actions on pipeline elements
- Move your mouse pointer over a pipeline element and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAQAAAAQCAIAAAC+1EmkAAAABmJLR0QA/wD/AP+gvaeTAAAACXBIWXMAAA7EAAAOxAGVKw4bAAAAQklEQVQImcWMwQ2AQAzDzHErdKmukq6TUTpfeSAhmIC8LNnKOTMRkZndvW1XFQAsXtuSbpJ0zMxjPtkCbNsGfnm7AHoKI+pR1PbRAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC) to expand the context menu; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required action:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Edit**

Open the resource in the dedicated editor.

> Note

For more information, see: [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAASCAIAAADUsmlHAAAABmJLR0QA/wD/AP+gvaeTAAAACXBIWXMAAA7EAAAOxAGVKw4bAAAAZ0lEQVQ4jdVSsQ3AMAizqt7DBfzAHxzEYfwAb7RDlwyJhJSiqp6QGYyNcRUQESIiIhEx8gc2cGamqrr7dE1EZvbM7s7MI7+ljM88o6KwwttpExGAyhd+6nn558oVDWlP+zyis9vtnm91mnZQJS4+hAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==)

**Details**

Open the Details panel to view and edit the resource's details.

> Note

For more information, see [Viewing and editing the details of a resource](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-pipeline-editor#viewing-and-editing-the-details-of-a-resource) below.

> Tip

When the Details panel is open, it is possible to view the details of another resource by clicking on a different element in the pipeline editor or resource in the project explorer panel.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Remove**

Remove the resource from the pipeline.

> Note

The resource will still be available in the project, and can be put back into the pipeline or permanently deleted.

For more information, see: [DT3 Project Explorer Panel.](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-project-explorer-panel)

### Viewing and editing the details of a resource
- Move your mouse pointer over the name of a resource in the project explorer panel (or over a pipeline element) and click the  ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon that appears to display the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Details**). The **Details **panel is displayed on the right; for example:![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- View and edit the required properties.

**Field**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the resource displayed in the **Resources **section on the left and in the pipeline, if in use 

> Important

The name of the resource must be unique in the pipeline.

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the resource

**Type**

*(only available for Reader and Writer resources)*

Select the resource type from the drop-down menu.

**Included in flow**

Automatically generated list of the flows that include this resource. 

> Tip

Click on the name of a flow to highlight it in the pipeline.

## Managing the pipeline
### Adding a new element to the pipeline
- Move your mouse pointer over a pipeline element; the  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) icon appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) to expand the context menu, displaying the element types that may be added after the selected pipeline element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required element type to add to the pipeline; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The new resource is added to the pipeline.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to configure pipeline elements, see: [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

### Connecting pipeline elements
- Move your mouse pointer over a disconnected pipeline element; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Drag &amp; drop it over a compatible pipeline element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The resource is added to the pipeline.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Rearranging pipeline elements
- Move your mouse pointer over a pipeline element; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Drag &amp; drop it over a compatible pipeline element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The resource and all the elements connected to it in the pipeline are moved to their new position.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

The graphical layout of pipeline elements is automatic and cannot be modified manually.

### Disconnecting pipeline elements
To disconnect an element from the pipeline, drag &amp; drop it away from its current position; for example:![](data:image/png;base64,)

The element is disconnected but still visible on the pipeline.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

This action will disconnected the selected element and all the elements connected to it in the pipeline.

> Note

For more information on how to remove an element from the pipeline, see [Actions on pipeline elements](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-pipeline-editor#actions-on-pipeline-elements) above.
